            <section id="gdpr" class="legal-section">
                <h2>GDPR Compliance & Data Protection</h2>
                <p class="last-updated">Last updated: 20th September 2025</p>

                <p>ClearFuneralCosts is committed to compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and UK data protection laws. This section outlines your rights and our obligations under these regulations.</p>

                <h3>Your Data Protection Rights</h3>
                <p>Under GDPR and UK GDPR, you have comprehensive rights regarding your personal data:</p>

                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Right of Access:</strong> Request copies of your personal data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> Limit how we process your data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a structured format</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to processing for specific purposes</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent for data processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Rights regarding Automated Decision Making:</strong> Human intervention in automated processes</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <h4>Exercising Your Rights</h4>
                    <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact our Data Protection Officer at privacy@clearfuneralcosts.co.uk. We will respond within one month of your request, free of charge.</p>
                </div>

                <h3>Lawful Basis for Processing</h3>
                <p>We process your personal data under the following lawful bases:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Consent:</strong> For marketing communications and optional services</li>
                    <li><strong>Contract:</strong> To provide our funeral cost information services</li>
                    <li><strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> For service improvement and fraud prevention</li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> To comply with CMA reporting requirements</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>International Data Transfers</h3>
                <p>Your personal data may be transferred to and processed in countries outside the UK/EEA. When this occurs, we ensure adequate protection through:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission</li>
                    <li>Adequacy decisions for data transfers to approved countries</li>
                    <li>UK International Data Transfer Agreement (IDTA)</li>
                    <li>Binding Corporate Rules for transfers within corporate groups</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Regulatory Compliance Framework</h3>
                
                <h4>Competition and Markets Authority (CMA)</h4>
                <p>Our data processing activities comply with the CMA Funerals Market Investigation Order 2021:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use of CMA-mandated funeral director pricing data</li>
                    <li>Transparency in our cost comparison methodologies</li>
                    <li>Independence from funeral director commercial interests</li>
                    <li>Public reporting of pricing analysis methods</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</h4>
                <p>ClearFuneralCosts maintains active registration with the ICO. For data protection concerns beyond our direct control, you can contact:</p>
                
                <div class="contact-info">
                    <strong>ICO Contact Information:</strong><br>
                    Website: <a href="https://ico.org.uk" class="external-link" target="_blank">ico.org.uk</a><br>
                    Phone: 0303 123 1113<br>
                    Post: Information Commissioner's Office, Wycliffe House, Water Lane, Wilmslow, Cheshire SK9 5AF
                </div>

                <h3>Data Breach Response</h3>
                <p>In the unlikely event of a data breach that may result in high risk to your rights and freedoms, we will:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Notify the ICO within 72 hours of becoming aware</li>
                    <li>Inform affected individuals without undue delay</li>
                    <li>Provide clear information about the breach and our response</li>
                    <li>Offer guidance on protective measures you can take</li>
                    <li>Provide regular updates on our investigation and remediation</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Special Category Data</h3>
                <p>We do not intentionally collect special category data (health, religious beliefs, etc.). If such information is provided voluntarily in communications, we:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Process it only for the specific purpose provided</li>
                    <li>Apply additional security measures</li>
                    <li>Delete it as soon as reasonably possible</li>
                    <li>Never share it with third parties</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Children's Privacy</h3>
                <p>Our services are not intended for children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware that a child has provided personal data, we will take immediate steps to delete such information.</p>

                <h3>Automated Decision Making and Profiling</h3>
                <p>Our funeral cost analysis involves automated processing to generate recommendations. You have the right to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Request human intervention in the decision-making process</li>
                    <li>Express your point of view regarding automated decisions</li>
                    <li>Contest decisions made solely by automated means</li>
                    <li>Receive an explanation of the logic involved</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Data Protection by Design and Default</h3>
                <p>We implement data protection principles from the ground up:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Privacy-first system architecture</li>
                    <li>Data minimisation practices</li>
                    <li>Regular privacy impact assessments</li>
                    <li>Staff training on data protection principles</li>
                </ul>

